## 4. Global State Management — `ApplicationContext`

A single React Context (`ApplicationContext`) provides all shared state and actions to the dashboard pages. **No Redux or Zustand used.**

### State Variables

| State | Type | Purpose |
|-------|------|---------|
| `applicationId` | `string \| null` | Current loan application UUID (persisted in `sessionStorage`) |
| `ucsoData` | `object \| null` | Full application data payload from backend (UCSO = Unified Credit Scoring Object) |
| `agentFeed` | `array` | Live WebSocket messages from AI agents (max 50, newest first) |
| `isCreating` | `boolean` | Loading flag during application creation |
| `createError` | `string \| null` | Error message from failed application creation |
| `loading` | `boolean` | Loading flag during data refresh |
| `wsConnected` | `boolean` | Whether WebSocket connection is active |

### Context Actions (consumed by pages)

| Action | What It Does |
|--------|-------------|
| [createApplication(formData)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#27-34) | Sends applicant data to backend, stores returned `applicationId` |
| `refreshApplication(id?)` | Fetches latest full application data |
| [addNote(noteData)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#42-48) | Submits a credit officer note |
| [submitPD(pdData)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#49-55) | Submits a Personal Discussion transcript |
| [triggerStress(stressData)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#56-64) | Triggers a financial stress simulation |
| [uploadDocument(file, type, onProgress)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#65-87) | Uploads a PDF/document via multipart form |
| `pushAgentUpdate(update)` | Manually pushes a message to the live feed |

### WebSocket Auto-Connect

When `applicationId` is set, the context **automatically**:
1. Connects to the backend WebSocket via STOMP+SockJS
2. Subscribes to `/topic/agent-updates` (global topic)
3. Filters messages client-side by `application_id`
4. Pushes matching updates into `agentFeed`
5. Auto-refreshes full application data when an agent's `status === 'completed'`

