## 5. Services Layer

### 5.1 REST Client — [api.js](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js)

- Uses **Axios** with a configurable `BASE_URL` (from `VITE_API_BASE_URL` env var, defaults to `http://localhost:8080`)
- Includes `ngrok-skip-browser-warning: true` header for dev tunnelling

**`ApplicationService` methods:**

| Method | HTTP | Endpoint | Request Body |
|--------|------|----------|-------------|
| [createApplication(data)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#27-34) | POST | `/api/application` | JSON map of applicant fields |
| [getApplication(id)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#35-41) | GET | `/api/application/{id}` | — |
| [addNote(id, data)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#42-48) | POST | `/api/application/{id}/notes` | `{ author, note, timestamp }` |
| [submitPD(id, data)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#49-55) | POST | `/api/application/{id}/pd` | `{ interviewer, transcript, pd_date }` |
| [triggerStress(id, data)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#56-64) | POST | `/api/application/{id}/stress` | `{ revenue_shock_pct, interest_rate_hike_bps, working_capital_squeeze_pct, raw_material_inflation_pct }` |
| [uploadDocument(id, file, type, onProgress)](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#65-87) | POST | `/api/files/upload` | `FormData: { file, application_id, type }` |

**Document types enum (must match backend):**

| Key | Label |
|-----|-------|
| `ANNUAL_REPORT` | Annual Report |
| `BANK_STMT` | Bank Statement |
| `GST_RETURN` | GST Return |
| `ITR` | ITR Filing |

### 5.2 WebSocket — [websocket.js](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/websocket.js)

- Uses **STOMP.js** over **SockJS** transport
- Connects to `{BASE_URL}/ws`
- Subscribes to topic: `/topic/agent-updates`
- Reconnect delay: 5000ms
- Messages filtered client-side by `application_id`

**Expected WebSocket message format (from backend):**

```json
{
  "application_id": "uuid-string",
  "agent": "Agent Name",
  "status": "COMPLETED | RUNNING | IN_PROGRESS | FAILED | ERROR",
  "message": "Human-readable status text",
  "timestamp": "ISO-8601 datetime"
}
```

