### 6.2 Data Ingestor Page (`/ingestor`)

**File:** [DataIngestor.jsx](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/pages/DataIngestor.jsx) + [DataIngestor.css](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/pages/DataIngestor.css) (~496 lines JSX, ~14KB CSS)

**Purpose:** Step 1 in the credit appraisal workflow. Create a loan application and upload the required 4 financial documents.

**Two-phase workflow:**

#### Phase 1 — Application Form (shown when NO `applicationId` exists)

A **14-field form** in a 2-column grid layout:

| Field Key | Label | Type | Required |
|-----------|-------|------|----------|
| `name` | Company / Applicant Name | text | ✅ |
| `business_name` | Business Name | text | ✅ |
| `pan` | PAN Number | text | ✅ |
| `cin` | CIN | text | ✅ |
| `mobile` | Mobile Number | tel | ✅ |
| `email` | Email Address | email | ✅ |
| `gst_number` | GST Number | text | ✅ |
| `loan_amount` | Loan Amount (₹) | number | ✅ |
| `loan_type` | Loan Type | text | ✅ |
| `annual_turnover` | Annual Turnover (₹) | number | ✅ |
| `sector` | Industry Sector | text | ✅ |
| `incorporation_year` | Incorporation Year | number | ❌ |
| `employee_count` | Employee Count | number | ❌ |
| `requested_tenure_months` | Requested Tenure (months) | number | ❌ |

**On submit:** numeric fields are converted to `Number`, empty optional fields removed, then sent to backend. On success, `applicationId` is stored.

#### Phase 2 — Document Uploads (shown AFTER `applicationId` exists)

**Application ID Badge** — displayed at top after creation

**4 Individual Document Upload Slots (in a grid):**

Each slot supports:
- Drag-and-drop
- File selection dialog (accepts `.pdf, .xlsx, .csv, .xls, .doc, .docx`)
- Individual upload with progress bar
- Status indicators: idle → selected → uploading → completed / error
- Re-upload capability
- "Upload All Selected" batch button

| Slot | Key | Description |
|------|-----|-------------|
| 📄 Annual Report | `ANNUAL_REPORT` | Company annual financial report |
| 🏦 Bank Statement | `BANK_STMT` | 12-month bank statement |
| 📊 GST Return | `GST_RETURN` | GST return filings |
| 📋 ITR Filing | `ITR` | Income Tax Return |

**Combined Upload Section:**
- Alternative single PDF upload for all 4 documents combined
- Same drag-and-drop + progress UX
- Uploads as `ANNUAL_REPORT` type

**Summary Cards (bottom):**
- 4 stat cards: Uploaded count, Selected count, Failed count, Required total (always 4)

---

### 6.3 Research Agent Page (`/research`)

**File:** [ResearchAgent.jsx](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/pages/ResearchAgent.jsx) + [ResearchAgent.css](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/pages/ResearchAgent.css) (~440 lines JSX, ~12KB CSS)

**Purpose:** Step 2 — the AI intelligence hub. Displays live agent results, risk scoring, and provides credit officer input tools.

**Guard:** If no `applicationId`, shows a "No Application Found" message directing user to Data Ingestor.

**Layout:** 2-column grid (`research-grid`)

#### Left Column — Live Agent Intelligence Feed

| Element | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| **Alert Banner** | Shown when `defaultProb` (default probability) exists — displays risk classification from AI Risk Agent |
| **Feed Header** | "Live Agent Intelligence Feed" with Refresh button |
| **Feed Items** | Expandable accordion items from `agentFeed` (WebSocket). Each shows: icon (color-coded by status), agent name, status, timestamp. Click to expand for full message body. Falls back to static "Awaiting Agent Results" message when no feed. |
| **AgentFeedWidget** | Embedded WebSocket live feed component (see Components section) |

#### Right Column — Officer Input Tools

| Card | Purpose | Fields Sent |
|------|---------|-------------|
| **Risk Score Card** | Animated SVG ring showing AI confidence score (0–100). Color-coded: ≥75 green (Low Risk), ≥50 yellow (Medium), <50 red (High). Recalibrate button triggers data refresh. | — (display only) |
| **Credit Officer Notes** | Input for officer observations. Submits via [addNote()](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/services/api.js#42-48). Shows list of previously submitted notes. | `{ author, note, timestamp }` |
| **Personal Discussion (PD)** | Interview transcript submission form. Fields: Interviewer name, date, transcript text. | `{ interviewer, transcript, pd_date }` |
| **Stress Simulation** | 4 numeric parameter sliders for financial scenario testing. | `{ revenue_shock_pct, interest_rate_hike_bps, working_capital_squeeze_pct, raw_material_inflation_pct }` |

**Stress Simulation defaults:**
- Revenue Shock: -20%
- Interest Rate Hike: 200 bps
- Working Capital Squeeze: -15%
- Raw Material Inflation: 10%

---

### 6.4 Recommendation Engine Page (`/recommendation`)

**File:** [RecommendationEngine.jsx](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/pages/RecommendationEngine.jsx) + [RecommendationEngine.css](file:///d:/Hackathon%20stuff/IITH-Hackathon/intelli-credit/src/pages/RecommendationEngine.css) (~411 lines JSX, ~10KB CSS)

**Purpose:** Step 3 — final decision output dashboard with visualizations and CAM report generation.

**Guard:** If no `applicationId`, shows "No Application Found" message.

**Auto-refresh:** Polls backend every 30 seconds if `ucsoData.risk` is empty/incomplete.

**Sections (top → bottom):**

#### Score Cards Row (4 cards)

| Card | Data Source | Display |
|------|------------|---------|
| **Intelli-Credit Score** | `derived_features.credit_score` or `risk.agent_confidence × 900` | Value / 900 |
| **Loan Amount** | `applicant.loan_amount` | Formatted in Lakhs (₹) |
| **Interest Rate** | `derived_features.suggested_rate` | Percentage |
| **Risk Assessment** | `risk.default_probability` + `risk.risk_grade` | Low/Medium/High + Grade |

#### Main Grid (2 columns)

**Left — AI Decision Logic Panel:**
- Displays SHAP (Shapley Additive Explanations) values from `ucsoData.risk.shap_values`
- Each SHAP feature rendered as an item with icon, title, and contribution percentage
- Falls back to placeholder items if no SHAP data available
- **"Generate CAM Report" button** — triggers CAM generation (currently frontend-only state toggle)
- When generated: shows download card for `CAM_Report.pdf`

**Right — Charts Panel:**

| Chart | Library | Data Source |
|-------|---------|-------------|
| **Assessment Breakdown** (Bar Chart) | Recharts `BarChart` | Cash Flow, Debt Ratio, Market Position, Management Score, Compliance — from `ucsoData.derived_features`, `ucsoData.financials`, `ucsoData.compliance` |
| **Risk Distribution** (Donut Chart) | Recharts `PieChart` | Strong/Moderate/Weak distribution — derived from `risk.agent_confidence` |

**Agent Feed Widget** — embedded below the charts

**Activity Log Section:**
- Recent activity derived from `agentFeed` (last 8 items)
- Each item shows: status dot (color-coded), agent name, message, timestamp
- Refresh button

